title: Yosemite
body: Yosemite National Park is a national park spanning portions of Tuolumne, Mariposa and Madera counties in Northern California.

title: Sequoia National Park
body: Sequoia National Park is a national park in the southern Sierra Nevada east of Visalia, California, in the United States.

title: Joshua Tree National Park
body: Joshua Tree National Park is located in southeastern California.  It is named for the Joshua trees native to the park. It covers a land area of 790,636 acresâ€”an area slightly larger than the state of Rhode Island.

title: Lake Tahoe
body: Lake Tahoe is a large freshwater lake in the Sierra Nevada of the United States. Lying at, it straddles the border between California and Nevada, west of Carson City. Lake Tahoe is the largest alpine lake in North America, and at trails only the five Great Lakes as the largest by volume in the United States.

title: Death Valley
body: Death Valley is a desert valley located in Eastern California. It is one of the hottest places in the world at the height of summertime.
